Here is the plain text of the problem statement:

```text
Time Limit: 5 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description

Given a number N and two arrays A, B of N numbers. Determine if B is a permutation of A or not.

Note: A permutation is an arrangement of all or part of a set of objects.

For example: The arrays [2,1,3], [3,2,1], and [2,3,1] are permutations of the array [1,2,3].

Input Format

The first line contains T, the number of test cases.

For each test case:

- The first line contains an integer N, the number of elements in the arrays A and B.
- The second line contains N space-separated integers each denoting an element of the array A.
- The third line contains N space-separated integers each denoting an element of the array B.

Output Format

Print "yes" if array B is a permutation of A, otherwise print "no" without quotations.

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 10
1 ≤ N ≤ 3 × 10^5
1 ≤ Ai ≤ 10^7
1 ≤ Bi ≤ 10^7

It's guaranteed that the sum of N over all test cases does not exceed 3 × 10^5.

Sample Input 1

1
4
4 2 3 7
2 3 4 9

Sample Output 1

no

Sample Input 2

2
4
4 2 3 7
2 3 4 9
5
5 1 1 9 3
1 9 1 5 3

Sample Output 2

no
yes

Note

In Sample Input 1, after sorting both arrays, they are not equal. Therefore, the output is "no".

In Sample Input 2:
- For the first test case, similar to Sample Input 1, the arrays are not equal after sorting, so the output is "no".
- For the second test case, after sorting, both arrays are equal, so the output is "yes".
```


#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(NULL);
    int t;
    cin>>t;
    while(t--)
    {
        int n;
        cin>>n;
        vector<int>a(n);
        vector<int>b(n);
        unordered_map<int,int>mp;

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            cin>>a[i];
            mp[a[i]]++;
        }

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            cin>>b[i];
            mp[b[i]]--;
        }
        
        
        bool isEqual = true;
        for(auto it : mp)
        {
            if(it.second != 0)
            {
                isEqual = false;
                break;
            }
        }

        if(isEqual)
            cout<<"yes"<<endl;
        else   
            cout<<"no"<<endl;

    }
    return 0;
}
